latestIgtvVideos.title: March On Washington
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It's hard to believe that a year's gone by since Tony's and @headcount teamed up to hand out march supplies and register voters at the March on Washington. Moments like this one continue to inspire us, 'cause it's not every day you get to see thousands of people standing up for what they believe in at once. 

That's why we're proud to continue the work with our friends at HeadCount. 'Cause protecting the right to vote is always critical. So keep an eye out for team HeadCount at the March on Washington tomorrow, and say hello to stay engaged and grab some Tony's 🍫

latestIgtvVideos.title: Golden Seeds​
latestIgtvVideos.caption: A story of hope, dreams, and yes, also hardships.. a story of the cocoa industry, as told by the farmers themselves. Beautifully captured by Ghanaian filmmaker David Boanuh in this short documentary celebrating a fresh, West African perspective. Brought to you by Tony's Chocolonely, because every story has multiple voices, and a more equitable future is only possible when every voice is heard.​

latestIgtvVideos.title: Save The Vote
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Fairness is something we can all get behind. And you already know how important we believe making your voice heard is. That's why we're standing with our friends at HeadCount to #SaveTheVote. 

Voting in the United States is challenging to say the least. That's why @headcountorg is challenging the status quo and aiming to generate action: 50,000 calls and emails to the state-level lawmakers who have the power to expand voter access or, sadly, roll it back.

Are you in?

latestIgtvVideos.title: Chocolloquium Episode 5: Saikat Chakrabarti
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Like us, @saikat_chakrabarti strongly believes that to change the world, you need to tackle the problems, not the symptoms. And to shake the system, he went straight to its heart: politics. Through the Brand New Congress scheme, Saikat helped launch 100s of progressive candidates in congressional races, including NY representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (AOC), and initiated the Green New Deal for tackling climate change. Because why not try!​
​
Get in on Saikat’s can-do attitude to change as he joins host @ameliahoy in our final episode of Tony’s Chocolloquium. 10 minutes. 2 changemakers. 1 sweet solution. Because a fair world needs more than just fair chocolate.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Chocolloquium Episode 4: Chetna Gala Sinha
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ever wondered what life would be like without a bank account? You can’t save. You can’t plan ahead. You can't invest in progress. Welcome to the world of millions of cocoa farmers. And millions of women in India – before Chetna Gala Sinha stepped in to create the world’s first rural women’s bank. Like her customers, she heard “no” more times than she could count, but that only helped her build momentum for her cause. ​

Curious how to turn your courage into capital? Tune in to our IGTV to see Chetna in conversation with @ameliahoy in Episode 4 of Tony’s Chocolloquium. 10 minutes. 2 changemakers. 1 sweet solution. Because a fair world needs more than just fair chocolate.​

latestIgtvVideos.title: Tony's Chocolloquium Episode 3: Jehiel Oliver - Disrupting Ecosystems
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Wise words from Jehiel Oliver, founder of shared economy platform @hellotractor and our next guest on Tony’s Chocolloquium – talking sweet solutions with serious changemakers. Because although "the forgotten continent” is home to some of the world’s biggest social issues, it’s also home to the bright young minds who are solving them. ​

Join Jehiel and host @ameliahoy in conversation to find out how Jehiel is disrupting and reshaping the outdated agricultural ecosystem in Africa and beyond to help farmers thrive. Because a fairer world needs more than just fair chocolate.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Dana’s Bakery “Perfect 10” Chocolate Brownies
latestIgtvVideos.caption: The hunt is over: we’ve found the tastiest brownie recipe ever! Join Tony’s Collegiate Changemakers in baking 3 versions of the most delicious brownies from @danasbakery’s new cookbook. 🍫 All made with Tony’s, of course. 😉 Bon appétit!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Episode 2 - Borre Akkersdijk
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Transparency is not just a serious issue in the chocolate supply chain. Just ask textile revolutionary @borreakkersdijk who’s been leading the way for change in the worlds of fashion and interiors. So, ehh, how do you demand transparency in industries that just aren’t interested? ​

Find out with Borre and @ameliahoy in Episode 2 of Tony’s Chocolloquium. 10 minutes. 2 changemakers. 1 sweet solution. Because a fair world needs more than just fair chocolate.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Tony's Chocolloqium | Episode 1
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Be the change you want to see.. but ehh, first, see the changemaker you wanna be inspired by! Meet campaigner, speaker, writer, lawmaker and upskirting activist @ginamartin. She’s got some awesome tips for anyone who wants to make a change, no matter how small. 

Tune in to see Gina in conversation with @ameliahoy in Episode 1 of Tony’s Chocolloquium. 10 minutes. 2 changemakers. 1 sweet solution. Because a fair world needs more than just fair chocolate.
 

#TonysChocolloquium

latestIgtvVideos.title: A sweet solution to a bitter truth
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Modern slavery and illegal child labor in 2021? How is this still happening? Here’s the answer.. and a little taste of how things could be so much sweeter if all chocolate companies and all choco fans worked together to make 100% slave free the norm in chocolate. Are you in? Sign the petition in the link in our bio​. 

#SweetSolution #Tonyschocolonely

latestIgtvVideos.title: It’s time to vote
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It's been a long road to get to this moment, from the primaries, to registration, to debates and more. Now, it's time to vote and make your voice heard! Visit our website using the link in our bio for resources to make your voice count in the 2020 elections.

Thank you to all of our friends that helped us make an impact this year: @headcountorg @just @somethinginthewater @thegoodsmart @twpthemovement @r.beats_ @mymamaskitchenva @chevyt00heavy @alexkcolby @thehoopbus @favorednations @blessyoufilms @glblctzn @greenpointfridge @stephwalterstv @harryperryband @brooklynbowl to name just a few 🙌🍫

latestIgtvVideos.title: Make Your Voice Heard - March on Washington
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It's not every day that you get to see tens of thousands of people standing up for what they believe in at once. We'd say "take it from us, it's a really powerful thing to witness" but we thought it'd be better just to show you.
 
Tony's went to the March on Washington with HeadCount and Favored Nations to inspire folks to register to vote, but we left inspired by the outspoken people we met there too. See for yourself!
 
And while you're here, make sure you're registered to vote too using the link in our bio.

#tonyschocolonely

latestPosts.caption:
Ready to unwrap more of Tony’s? We’re peeling back the layers of all the goods we have to share - from our irresistible chocolate to our unstoppable impact. From LA to NYC, from popups to partnerships to totally transparent content series, we’re about to bring the goods to you.

So what do you say, are you in?

We’re over the choco-moon to announce the launch of Lil' Bits – our new delicious, munchable chocolate range that's ending exploitation in cocoa by paying cocoa farmers a fair price. ✊ 

Ohhhh yeah, chocolate lovers finally have a responsibly sourced, bite-size chocolate option to chomp on. 🤤 Dig into Lil’ Bits’ chewy crunchy cores wrapped in thick, chunky chocolate. Now available in these 3 crazy tasty flavors..

🍫 triple chocolate mix
🧡 milk caramel sea salt & cookie mix
🍪 milk s'mores mix

So grab a handful and support our mission to end exploitation in cocoa.

Shop now via the link in our bio (or find 'em on @wholefoods shelves near you).

latestPosts.caption:
Okay, we're fangirling over here! 🥹 

Last night, John Oliver @lastweektonight dedicated their episode to shedding light on the bitter truth about the chocolate industry while highlighting some sweet solutions to the problem. Just in time for Halloween! 

We may be biased, but unwrapping the issues within the chocolate industry leads to a straightforward solution: enabling cocoa farmers to earn a living income! It’s so clear.. even an impact company mistaken for a clown restaurant can do it! 🌃🍫 

What late night show do you wanna see cover the issues in cocoa next?

latestPosts.caption:
Big (choco) News! 🍫📢 We are proud to be included on @time list of the 100 Most Influential Companies of 2025! 

Influence was never the goal. Ending exploitation in the cocoa industry was, and still is, our mission. 

At Tony’s, we aim to raise awareness, lead by example, and inspire others to act. 

If our mission, our chocolate, and our actions are inspiring others to join the movement, then we’re on the right path. ❤️

Because real change takes all of us.🤝🏻✨

#TIME100Companies
